President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has approved a disaster declaration for the Salt River Pima-Maricopa Indian Community in Arizona. The declaration provides federal aid to supplement the Tribe's efforts in the areas affected by severe storms that occurred on July 17-18, 2022. This includes grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to help individuals and business owners recover from the disaster. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Deanne Criswell, Administrator of FEMA, has named Andrew F. Grant as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners can apply for assistance by registering online or calling the designated phone numbers. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.